  "text": "This answer identifies rate limiting implementations across two major cloud infrastructure projects:\n\n**Envoy Proxy Rate Limiting Pattern:**\nEnvoy implements a dual-layer rate limiting architecture:\n1. **Local Rate Limiting (Token Bucket)**: The HTTP local rate limit filter (source/extensions/filters/http/local_ratelimit/) implements token bucket-based rate limiting at the filter level. The FilterConfig class initializes with token_bucket configuration parameters (max_tokens, tokens_per_fill, fill_interval). The underlying implementation in source/extensions/filters/common/local_ratelimit/local_ratelimit_impl.cc provides the LocalRateLimiterImpl class that manages token bucket state and share mechanisms for distributed setups.\n\n2. **Global Rate Limiting (Service Client)**: Envoy's global rate limiting is implemented through a gRPC-based service client. The GrpcClientImpl class in source/extensions/filters/common/ratelimit/ratelimit_impl.cc handles communication with external rate limit services via the RateLimitService.ShouldRateLimit method. The HTTP rate limit filter (source/extensions/filters/http/ratelimit/) serves as the filter integration point that calls this service client to make rate limiting decisions based on request descriptors and domain configurations.\n\n**Kubernetes API Server Rate Limiting (APF - Adaptive Priority and Fairness):**\n1. **Token Bucket Rate Limiter**: The client-go package provides token bucket implementation (staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/flowcontrol/throttle.go) with the tokenBucketPassiveRateLimiter structure that wraps golang.org/x/time/rate.Limiter for client-side rate limiting. This provides TryAccept() and Accept() methods for rate limiting decisions.\n\n2. **Priority Level Handling**: The APF controller (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/util/flowcontrol/apf_controller.go) manages PriorityLevel resources from the flowcontrol API, handling status updates and priority level lifecycle. The APF filter (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/util/flowcontrol/apf_filter.go) implements the main request handling interface that classifies requests and directs them through priority levels.\n\n3. **Fair Queuing Implementation**: The queueset implementation (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/util/flowcontrol/fairqueuing/queueset/queueset.go) provides fair queuing across priority levels with the queueSetFactory creating QueueSet objects that handle request queuing, dispatch, and resource allocation according to configured concurrency limits and fair queuing parameters.\n\nBoth systems use token bucket algorithms as the fundamental rate limiting mechanism but apply them at different levels: Envoy at the filter/gateway level for request-based rate limiting, and Kubernetes at the API server level for connection and concurrency-based rate limiting with sophisticated priority and fairness semantics."
}

